$ fatfs --help
Usage: fatfs [OPTIONS] DISKIMAGE COMMAND [ARGUMENTS]
Create or manipulate the contents of a FAT-formatted disk image.
For help about a specific command, run `fatfs x help COMMAND`.

Options:
    -v              Verbose output.
    --help          Print this help menu and exit.
    --version       Print program version information and exit.

Commands:
    add             Add files to the disk image.
    attr            Change file attributes.
    copy            Copy the contents of a file or directory.
    create          Create a new FAT-formatted disk image.
    extract         Extract files from the disk image.
    help            Print help about a command.
    info            Print file, directory, or disk information.
    list            Print the contents of a directory.
    mkdir           Create a directory.
    move            Move a file or directory to a new location.
    remove          Remove a file or directory.
    rename          Rename a file or directory.
    touch           Change file access and modification times.
    type            Print the contents of a file.

Examples:
    $ fatfs floppy.img create
    $ fatfs floppy.img create -L "MY DISK" --force

    $ fatfs floppy.img add MYFILE.TXT
    $ fatfs floppy.img add -d DIR0 MYFILE.TXT
    $ fatfs floppy.img add -d DIR0/DIR01 -p MYFILE.TXT MYFILE2.TXT

    $ fatfs floppy.img copy MYFILE.TXT MYFILE3.TXT